<template><div><h1 id="json-rpc-api" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#json-rpc-api" aria-hidden="true">#</a> JSON-RPC API</h1>
<p>zkSync 2.0 fully supports the standard <a href="https://ethereum.org/en/developers/docs/apis/json-rpc/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Ethereum JSON-RPC API<ExternalLinkIcon/></a>, which means you can read blockchain data or send transactions to the Ethereum network.</p>
<p>However, zkSync 2.0 add some custom L2-specific features and methods to simplify certain zkSync-specific interactions, in this <RouterLink to="/api/api.html#zksync-specific-json-rpc-methods">guide</RouterLink>, you'll learn about zkSync JSON-RPC methods</p>
</div></template>


